<Page
    x:Class="GdriveHandler.Pages.GuidePage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

    <ScrollViewer Padding="32,24,32,24">
        <StackPanel Spacing="12" MaxWidth="680" HorizontalAlignment="Left">

            <TextBlock Text="Guide &amp; Examples" Style="{StaticResource TitleTextBlockStyle}"/>

            <!-- Supported extensions -->
            <TextBlock Text="Supported extensions" Style="{StaticResource SubtitleTextBlockStyle}"
                       Margin="0,8,0,0"/>
            <TextBlock x:Name="ExtensionsText" IsTextSelectionEnabled="True"
                       Foreground="{ThemeResource TextFillColorSecondaryBrush}"/>

            <!-- Sample file -->
            <TextBlock Text="Sample shortcut file (.gsheet)" Style="{StaticResource SubtitleTextBlockStyle}"
                       Margin="0,8,0,0"/>
            <Border CornerRadius="8" Padding="12"
                    Background="{ThemeResource CardBackgroundFillColorDefaultBrush}"
                    BorderBrush="{ThemeResource CardStrokeColorDefaultBrush}" BorderThickness="1">
                <TextBox IsReadOnly="True" AcceptsReturn="True"
                         FontFamily="Consolas" FontSize="12"
                         TextWrapping="NoWrap" BorderThickness="0"
                         Background="Transparent"
                         AutomationProperties.AutomationId="SampleCodeBlock"
                         Text="{x:Bind SampleJson, Mode=OneTime}"/>
            </Border>

            <!-- How matching works -->
            <TextBlock Text="How matching works" Style="{StaticResource SubtitleTextBlockStyle}"
                       Margin="0,8,0,0"/>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" LineHeight="22">
1. Read the email address from the shortcut file.&#x0a;2. Scan every Chrome and Edge profile's Local State for an exact, case-insensitive match of profile.info_cache[&lt;profile&gt;].user_name.&#x0a;3. If a match is found, launch that exact profile with the correct URL.&#x0a;4. If no direct match, check the Aliases table: if the email maps to another email, retry step 2 with the mapped address.&#x0a;5. If still no match, open the URL in Chrome's currently-active profile (no --profile-directory flag), or the system default browser if Chrome is not installed.
            </TextBlock>

            <!-- Gmail → Workspace -->
            <TextBlock Text="Gmail → Workspace conversion" Style="{StaticResource SubtitleTextBlockStyle}"
                       Margin="0,8,0,0"/>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" LineHeight="22">
When a Gmail account is converted to Google Workspace (e.g. user@gmail.com → user@domain.fyi), Chrome's Local State records only the current email. Old Drive shortcut files that still embed the old address will not match.

Add an alias in the Aliases page:
  From: user@gmail.com
  To:   user@domain.fyi

gdriveHandler will then route old-address files to the converted profile.
            </TextBlock>

            <!-- Edge caveat -->
            <TextBlock Text="Edge caveat" Style="{StaticResource SubtitleTextBlockStyle}"
                       Margin="0,8,0,0"/>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" LineHeight="22">
A Chrome profile's signed-in identity is its Google account, so matching is reliable. An Edge profile's identity is its Microsoft account. A Google account merely browsed in an Edge web session is not recorded in Local State. Edge therefore only matches when the target email is the Edge profile's primary signed-in identity (common with Workspace / Entra AAD accounts). You can disable Edge matching in Settings if it causes false positives.
            </TextBlock>

        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
